CREATE TABLE model_evaluation_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE performance_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(255),
    execution_time INT,
    loss FLOAT,
    accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE comparison_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_1_id INT,
    model_2_id INT,
    metric VARCHAR(255),
    model_1_value FLOAT,
    model_2_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 model_name VARCHAR(50),
 accuracy FLOAT,
 precision FLOAT,
 recall FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE performance_results (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 model_id INT,
 evaluation_date DATE,
 processing_time INT,
 memory_usage INT
)

CREATE TABLE comparison_data (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 model_a_id INT,
 model_b_id INT,
 comparison_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE model_details (
 id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 model_name VARCHAR(50),
 description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE execution_logs (

)
